---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is MY a Scrabble Word? Yes! One of the Highest-Scoring 2-Letter Words (7 Points)"
  description="MY is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS, worth 7 points (M=3, Y=4). A possessive pronoun and one of the HIGHEST scoring two-letter words without premium squares."
  keywords="is my a scrabble word, my scrabble valid, my points scrabble, my twl sowpods, highest scoring two letter words, my 7 points scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is MY a Scrabble Word? Yes! One of the Highest-Scoring 2-Letter Words (7 Points)",
    "description": "MY is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS, worth 7 points. A possessive pronoun and one of the highest scoring two-letter words.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-my-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is MY a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! MY is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) dictionaries. At 7 points (M=3, Y=4), it's tied with BY as the highest-scoring two-letter word using common consonants." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is MY worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "MY is worth 7 points: M(3) + Y(4) = 7. This makes it one of the highest-scoring two-letter words available. Only QI (11pts) and ZA (11pts) score higher among universally valid 2-letter words." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the highest scoring two-letter word in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "In both dictionaries, QI and ZA score 11 points each. After that, XI and XU score 9 points. MY and BY are tied at 7 points as the highest-scoring 2-letter words using common tiles." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is MY a Scrabble Word? Yes! One of the Highest-Scoring 2-Letter Words</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">MY — the possessive pronoun we use a hundred times a day — is one of Scrabble's secret weapons. At 7 points, MY is tied with BY as the highest-scoring two-letter word that uses only common consonants. Both M(3) and Y(4) deliver premium value, making MY a go-to play when you want maximum points from minimum tiles.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">MY</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">7 points · M(3) + Y(4) · Possessive pronoun · TWL + SOWPODS</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">MY is one of the highest-scoring universally valid two-letter words. Only QI(11), ZA(11), XI(9), and XU(9) beat it — and those require rare Q, Z, or X tiles. MY uses common consonants for elite scoring.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">7</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">#5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Rank (Both Dicts)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">Tied BY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Same Score</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why MY Scores So High</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Scoring Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">MY combines two medium-value consonants — <span class="text-white font-medium">M(3) and Y(4)</span> — for a total of 7 points. Most 2-letter words score 2-5 points because they pair high-value letters with 1-point vowels. MY avoids this by using no vowels at all (Y acts as the vowel sound).</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Highest-Scoring 2-Letter Words (Both Dictionaries)</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QI</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZA</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XI</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XU</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts ★</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts ★</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">MY on Premium Squares</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Y on Double Letter</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Y(4×2) + M(3) = 11 points from just two tiles. Equivalent to playing QI without needing a Q tile!</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">M on Double Letter</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">M(3×2) + Y(4) = 10 points. Still excellent value from a simple two-letter word.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Play MY</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">No-vowel play:</span> MY uses no traditional vowels (Y acts as one). This means you keep all your A/E/I/O/U tiles for longer words while still scoring 7 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Cross-word generator:</span> Both M and Y form numerous two-letter cross-words (MA, ME, MI, MO, MU, MM + YA, YE, YO). MY is ideal for parallel plays scoring from multiple directions.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Endgame weapon:</span> At 7 points for 2 tiles (3.5 pts/tile), MY offers exceptional points-per-tile efficiency in tight endgames where every point counts.</p></div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-we-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is WE a Scrabble Word? 5-Point Pronoun Play</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-he-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is HE a Scrabble Word? Another High-Value Pronoun</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word's validity instantly — free, realtime, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
